You can use the Bean Validation Framework for this. 

1) Annotate the request object as needing validation:

    fun submit(@Valid @RequestBody formObject: FormObject): FormObject
               ^^^^^^

2) Annotate the fields of your data class with the appropriate validation annotations:

    data class FormObject(
        @field:NotBlank 
        val email: String, 

        @field:Min(1) 
        @field:Max(150) 
        val age: Int
    )

Note that you have to apply the annotation to the `field` (not the parameter) or the validation won&#39;t happen the way we want. Also, if we define `age` as an `Int`, it will have a default value (`0`) if the caller does not send it, so I applied a the minimum validation on that to offset that (assuming age 0 is not ok, YMMV).

